    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="https://raleigh.craigslist.org/apa/d/durham-sunny-large-3br-minutes-from/7512219730.html"></div>
        </div>
Incredibly sunny, expansive home for rent in a residential Durham neighborhood, 7 minutes from Duke and 15 from the University of North Carolina. <br>
<br>
Fully furnished, with quality furnishings, and excellent mattresses (Master BR is tempur-pedic). :) All linens included. Utilities included. The kitchen is stocked with appliances, dishes etc. Two dining tables. Brand new large refrigerator/freezer with filtered water and ice dispenser. ATT fiber internet. Wireless booster, and ethernet cable available. The laundry is at the foot of the stairs in the basement.<br>
<br>
Large living room perfect for entertaining and gatherings (modest and respectful only). 50" smart tv with wireless connection and Netflix. Available futons for temporary guests. <br>
<br>
Large master BR, large second BR. 3rd BR is small but sweet. Right now the master BR doesn't have a large desk. I will supply. I am renting out the room now and the renter requested minimal. <br>
<br>
4 car parking out front, and woods and picnic table at the back of the house. Quiet neighborhood. Half acre, and less than a mile from Duke Forest which has amazing hiking trails. Also, because we are so near the forest, we have deer, rabbits, hawks, owls. It's a sweet house and a sweet location. The house is also just 9 minutes from downtown Durham which is really cool, and the Durham Bulls stadium. The house is very close to Chapel Hill. <br>
<br>
<br>
I've been renting to scholars and adults for 28 years, and am a responsive landlord. I am onsite in the basement apartment and am always available if you need me. However, I will not intrude at all! I will only rent to respectful people who will not cause commotion in the neighborhood. Completely LGBTQ, race friendly. I don't use pesticides, and there is solar on the roof. You aren't responsible for yard care, but you are welcome to garden. The front of the house is not interesting, but am working on adding trees, a few flowers and ground cover. <br>
<br>
$1800 refundable deposit. If pets, an additional $1000 refundable pet deposit. If you leave the home fully clean, there will be no cleaning fee. If not, not a problem - I'll just deduct from your deposit what I have to pay plus my time. If you have a pet that is peeing on the floor or ripping furniture up, you'll have to leave. I'll be totally fair.<br>
<br>
If you are interested, I'm happy to show you the home in-person, or via video chat if you are not currently in the area. With video chat, I will also provide proof of the home, its availability and my ownership. <br>
<br>
90 day minimum, 60 days notice. As long as the house remains taken care of, your deposit will apply to your last month's rent. A 30 day rental is also fine, but is 3,500 for the month with a refundable $1,800 deposit. You'll receive it as soon as you leave. I don't think it is fair for deposits to be held up while folks need to move somewhere else.<br>
    </section>

